    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3327</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-09T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >July 9, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1526. Minister for Foreign Affairs informed my Chilean colleague<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d397fn27">Conrado Rios Gallardo.</note> today that Japanese
                        Ambassador<note n="28" xml:id="d397fn28">Shu Tomii.</note> called on him
                    yesterday and was even more menacing than at the time he called to protest
                    against Radio Communications decree. He cautioned the Minister against his
                    Government breaking relations with Japan, saying that they would defeat the
                    United States and would then retaliate against those countries which had taken
                    an unfriendly position. The Minister told him that if Japan proceeded against
                    any American country, Argentina would declare war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
